 DUTIES:
 Act as the principal designer for major systems and their subsystems utilizing a thorough understanding of available technology, tools and existing designs. Responsible for technical delivery of complex system design and development activities for a given assignment; act as lead technical resource responsible for directing the overall technical progress of projects or application initiatives; plan and administer the operational and administrative activities of a Development/Systems Analysis/ Programming unit or team; mentor the team in driving data analytics to the business; consult with functional management in the analysis of short and long-range business requirements and recommends innovations which anticipate the future impact of changing business needs; work closely with client management to identify and specify the complex business requirements and processes for diverse development platforms, computing environments (e.g., host based, distributed systems, client server), software, hardware, technologies and tools; provide highly technical consulting and leadership in identifying and implementing new uses of information technologies that assist the functional business units in meeting their strategic objectives; review the disaster recovery plan to ensure that new systems promote uninterrupted systems operation; coordinate activities with IT unit heads (e.g., database, operations, telecommunications, technical support, etc.); direct section staff responsible for all phases of the system development and implementation process including analysis, design, development, testing and ongoing support for the client areaâ€™s application systems in an environment of diverse development platforms, computing environments (e.g., host based, distributed systems, client server), software, hardware, technology and tools, etc.; act as primary technical point of contact for interaction with other units and teams; organize the activities of the section, assigns personnel to the various project or application components, and directs their activities; and, review, evaluate and prepare periodic activity and progress reports for the section.
