 Position requires a Masterâ€™s degree (or foreign equivalent) in Informatics, Computer Science or Information Technology, Bioinformatics, or a related field plus six (6) years of experience in the job offered or in a related position. Experience must include the following: Experience must include at least 6 years of working in IT systems analysis and application program development, or an equivalent combination of education and work experience; Demonstrable knowledge of the system development life cycle, the client areaâ€™s functions and systems, and application program development alternatives; Demonstrable experience working with the business in transforming the legacy IT tools and technologies, and with migration of existing applications to Amazon Web Services (AWS) Cloud; Demonstrable experience implementing POCâ€™s and on-board Snowflake and ThoughtSpot software tools for business; Demonstrable experience developing topic modeling for speech Analytics on call center data, and implementing machine learning and artificial intelligence algorithms in modeling; Demonstrable experience working on Genesys Integrated Voice Recognition Systems, IEX Scheduling System and Operations Performance Tracking Tools and develop code modules for providing data from these systems for analytical needs; Demonstrable experience developing data pipelines that ingest data from variety of source, transform/aggregate, and consume to downstream applications utilizing Avro, Parquet and other file formats; Demonstrable experience developing pipelines using Scala, Java, Python programming languages; using Apache Spark framework; Demonstrable experience conducting performance tuning and debugging spark applications; Demonstrable experience designing and Engineering scalable/robust data ingestion process that ingests data from multiple sources including structured data from Database Systems, semi-structured data from JSON documents; Demonstrable experience implementing the Continuous Integrat